########################################################################################################################
# Help for SSH connections
########################################################################################################################
⚠️  EXPERIMENTAL — not yet tested in a live environment.
    Please report any issues at https://github.com/Minhounet/nixlper/issues
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[CTRL + X then S] / sc   SSH connect — open the fzf picker, select a connection, and connect.
                          On first use with a new host, nixlper pushes your SSH key automatically
                          (you type your password once). Subsequent connections are passwordless.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[sca]  Add SSH connection — interactive prompt for label, user, host, port, and optional
       identity file. If no identity file is given, the global default is used.
       Global default key: ~/.ssh/nixlper_id_rsa  (generated on first connect if absent).
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[scr]  Remove SSH connection — fzf picker to choose which connection to delete.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[scl]  List SSH connections — tabular view of all saved connection profiles.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Configuration (nconf / CTRL+X+C):
  NIXLPER_SSH_CONNECTIONS_FILE  — path to the connections file
                                  (default: ~/.config/nixlper/ssh_connections)
  NIXLPER_SSH_IDENTITY_FILE     — default SSH key used when no per-connection key is set
                                  (default: ~/.ssh/nixlper_id_rsa)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Connection file format (one entry per line, # = comment):
  label|user|host|port|identity_file
  Example: myserver|alice|192.168.1.10|22|
  Leave identity_file empty to use NIXLPER_SSH_IDENTITY_FILE.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
